definition: adornment/to adorn/dress/clothing/costume (of an actor in a play)/to play a role/to pretend/to install/to fix/to wrap (sth in a bag)/to load/to pack

sentences.english: Dark shades bring edginess to summer dressing.
sentences.chinese: 暗色调为夏日衣装带来前卫感。

sentences.english: Clothes to people, to the Buddha Gold.
When Westies are born the ears are very small and stand up.
sentences.chinese: 当衣装生来耳朵非常小而站立起来。

sentences.english: We had the unfortunate experience to lose two of our Westies that dug under the fence.
sentences.chinese: 我们有不幸经历失去我们的两个衣装，挖下的栅栏。

sentences.english: Wheat and beef seem to cause some Westies to be more susceptible to grass allergies.
sentences.chinese: 小麦和牛肉似乎带来一些衣装向更容易草过敏。

sentences.english: Do not make yourself uneasy, my dear cousin, about your apparel.
sentences.chinese: 不要为衣装担心思，亲爱的表妹。

sentences.english: Men are vain; they will check themselves out in the mirror.
sentences.chinese: 男人们自负，他们只会在镜子前整理自己的衣装。

sentences.english: Bear in mind that I never bathe my Westies.
sentences.chinese: 记住，我从来不洗澡，我的衣装。

sentences.english: The Westies of that era had harsh white coats that were kept short by nature.
sentences.chinese: 衣装的那个时代了苛刻的白大衣，存放短期性质。

sentences.english: Westies have been spared the genetic problems associated with many of the other breeds.
sentences.chinese: 衣装已幸免遗传问题，与许多其他品种。

sentences.english: This is why we do not bath our Westies.
sentences.chinese: 这就是我们为什么不洗澡的衣装。

sentences.english: Westies have a lot of pride.
Westies live to please their masters.
sentences.chinese: 衣装活取悦自己的主人。

sentences.english: There are some lines of Westies have to have the ears of all their puppies taped.
sentences.chinese: 也有一些线路的衣装已经有耳其所有幼犬录播。

sentences.english: This really works, our many Westies have never had a flea in 25 years.
sentences.chinese: 这项工程的确，我们许多衣装从未有过跳蚤25年。
